Advocate Moipone Noko. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has accepted the North West Director of Public Prosecution's resignation.
Advocate Moipone Noko resigned after NPA boss Shamila Batohi instituted an inquiry into her fitness to hold office. READ: NPA dismisses Zuma trial delay statement Noko's troubles started when a panel, headed by Advocate Rodney de Kock, concluded that she had manipulated charges while serving as KZN's director of prosecutions. She dropped corruption charges against Durban businessman Toshan Panday in 2014. However, Noko's decision was overturned in 2016 by former NPA head Shaun Abrahams.  President agrees to resignation of North West Director of Public Prosecutions https://t.co/AtncUyKfgG